        "Download YT videos in 4K",
        "YT to MP3 converter",
        "No app needed",
        "100% free",
        "Works on all devices",
      ]}
    />

    <!-- Long-form SEO Content -->
    <section class="seo-section page-container">
      <div class="seo-long-form">
        <article class="seo-article">
          <h2 class="display-md">What is a YT Downloader?</h2>
          <p class="body-md">
            A <strong>YT downloader</strong> is an online tool that allows you to download videos from YouTube (commonly abbreviated as "YT") directly to your computer, phone, or tablet. Instead of streaming videos online and using your data every time, a <strong>yt video downloader</strong> lets you save videos permanently for offline viewing. mp4yt is the <strong>best yt downloader</strong> available in 2026 — it's completely free, works in any web browser, and requires zero software installation. Whether you want to save tutorials, music videos, documentaries, lectures, or vlogs, this <strong>yt downloader online</strong> tool makes it effortless.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="seo-article">
          <h2 class="display-md">How to Download YT Videos</h2>
          <p class="body-md">
            Using our <strong>YT video downloader</strong> is incredibly simple. Here's how to <strong>download yt videos</strong> in four easy steps:
          </p>
          <ol class="seo-steps">
            <li><strong>Copy the YouTube URL</strong> — Open YouTube in your browser or app, find the video you want, and copy the URL from the address bar or the share button.</li>
            <li><strong>Paste into mp4yt</strong> — Come to this page and paste the YouTube video URL into the extraction bar above.</li>
            <li><strong>Click Extract</strong> — Hit the "Extract" button and wait just a few seconds while our <strong>yt downloader</strong> fetches the direct download links.</li>
            <li><strong>Download</strong> — Choose your preferred quality (360p to 4K) or select MP3 for audio-only, then click download. That's it!</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="body-md">
            This entire process takes less than 30 seconds. No sign-up, no app installation, no limits — just a fast, free <strong>yt downloader</strong> that works.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="seo-article">
          <h2 class="display-md">YT to MP4 Converter</h2>
          <p class="body-md">
            Looking for a reliable <strong>yt to mp4</strong> converter? mp4yt delivers direct MP4 streams from YouTube's CDN, ensuring you get the highest possible quality without any re-encoding or compression. Our <strong>yt to mp4</strong> tool supports every resolution available on YouTube — from 360p standard definition all the way up to 2160p 4K Ultra HD. The downloaded MP4 files play on every device and media player, including VLC, Windows Media Player, QuickTime, and all mobile video players. Unlike other <strong>yt downloaders</strong> that re-encode and degrade quality, mp4yt preserves the original source quality.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="seo-article">
          <h2 class="display-md">YT to MP3 Converter</h2>
          <p class="body-md">
            Need just the audio? mp4yt doubles as a powerful <strong>yt to mp3</strong> converter. Extract high-quality audio from any YouTube video and save it as an MP3 file. Perfect for downloading music, podcasts, audiobooks, ASMR, nature sounds, lectures, and more. Our <strong>yt mp3 downloader</strong> preserves the original audio bitrate for crystal-clear playback. No separate app needed — this <strong>yt downloader</strong> handles both video and audio conversions in one place.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="seo-article">
          <h2 class="display-md">YT Downloader for iPhone & Android</h2>
          <p class="body-md">
            Searching for a <strong>yt downloader</strong> that works on your phone? mp4yt is fully optimized for mobile devices. Unlike traditional downloader apps that require installation and often contain ads or malware, our web-based <strong>yt video downloader</strong> runs entirely in your browser — Safari, Chrome, Firefox, or any mobile browser. On <strong>iPhone</strong>, after extracting the video, tap the download link and select "Save to Files" to store it locally. On <strong>Android</strong>, downloads start automatically. No app installation needed, no storage wasted on bloated software.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="seo-article">
          <h2 class="display-md">Best YT Downloader 2026</h2>
          <p class="body-md">
            Why is mp4yt considered the <strong>best yt downloader 2026</strong>? Because we built it with one goal: give users the fastest, simplest, and most reliable way to <strong>download yt videos</strong>. No AI bloat, no countdown timers, no CAPTCHAs, no speed limits, and no premium paywalls. Just paste your link and download. Our backend uses advanced stream extraction technology to fetch direct CDN links in milliseconds. And because we never store your files on our servers, your privacy is always protected. It's the <strong>yt video downloader</strong> that respects both your time and your privacy.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Dedicated YT FAQ -->
    <section id="faq" class="faq-band" aria-labelledby="yt-faq-headline">
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
      <div class="page-container faq-inner">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <span class="eyebrow">YT Downloader FAQ</span>
          <h2 id="yt-faq-headline" class="display-lg faq-title">
            Common questions about our YT downloader.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-list">
          {ytFaqs.map((faq) => (
            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary>
                <span class="body-md-strong">{faq.q}</span>
                <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M10 4v12M4 10h12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="faq-body">
                <p class="body-md" style="color: var(--color-body); margin: 0;">{faq.a}</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Internal linking section -->
    <section class="internal-links-section page-container">
      <div class="internal-links-grid">
        <div class="internal-link-card card">
          <h3 class="display-xs">More Downloaders</h3>
          <p class="body-sm" style="color: var(--color-body);">mp4yt isn't just a YT downloader — it also supports 1000+ other platforms:</p>
          <ul class="internal-links-list">
            <li><a href="/instagram">Instagram Video Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/tiktok">TikTok Video Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/twitter">Twitter/X Video Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/facebook">Facebook Video Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reddit">Reddit Video Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/vimeo">Vimeo Video Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/twitch">Twitch Clip Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/soundcloud">SoundCloud Downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/">All Platforms →</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="internal-link-card card">
          <h3 class="display-xs">Popular YT Downloader Searches</h3>
          <p class="body-sm" style="color: var(--color-body);">People also search for:</p>
          <ul class="internal-links-tags">
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">yt downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">yt video downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">download yt video</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">yt to mp4</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">yt to mp3</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">yt downloader free</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">yt downloader online</a></li>
            <li><a href="/yt-downloader">best yt downloader</a></li>
            <li><a href="/">video downloader</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Long-form SEO content */
  .seo-section {
    padding: var(--sp-4xl) var(--sp-lg);
    border-top: var(--border);
  }

  .seo-long-form {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3xl);
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .seo-article {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-md);
  }

  .seo-article h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .seo-article p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-body);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .seo-steps {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--sp-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-sm);
    color: var(--color-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* FAQ styles — brutalist */
  .faq-band {
    background-color: var(--color-canvas);
    padding: var(--sp-5xl) var(--sp-lg);
    border-top: var(--border);
  }

  .faq-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 340px 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-3xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .faq-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-sm);
    position: sticky;
    top: 80px;
  }

  .faq-title {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 300px;
  }

  .faq-list {
    border-top: var(--border);
  }

  details.faq-item {
    border-bottom: var(--border);
  }

  details.faq-item summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--sp-md);
    padding: var(--sp-lg) var(--sp-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-headline);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    transition: all 0.1s ease;
    user-select: none;
  }

  details.faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  details.faq-item summary::marker { display: none; }
  details.faq-item summary span {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: left;
  }
  details.faq-item summary:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-on-primary);
    padding-left: var(--sp-md);
    padding-right: var(--sp-md);
  }

  details.faq-item .faq-body {
    overflow: hidden;
    height: 0;
    transition: height 0.3s ease;
  }

  details.faq-item[open] .faq-body {
    height: auto;
    padding: 0 var(--sp-sm) var(--sp-lg);
  }

  .faq-icon {
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--color-mute);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, color 0.15s ease;
  }

  details.faq-item[open] .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  details.faq-item summary:hover .faq-icon {
    color: var(--color-on-primary);
  }

  /* Internal linking section */
  .internal-links-section {
    padding: var(--sp-4xl) var(--sp-lg);
    border-top: var(--border);
  }

  .internal-links-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    border: var(--border);
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    gap: 2px;
  }

  .internal-link-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-md);
    padding: var(--sp-xl);
    background-color: var(--color-canvas);
    border: none;
  }

  .internal-link-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .internal-links-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-xs);
  }

  .internal-links-list a {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-body);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.1s ease;
  }

  .internal-links-list a:hover {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .internal-links-tags {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--sp-xs);
  }

  .internal-links-tags li a {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    background-color: var(--color-canvas);
    border: var(--border);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.1s ease;
  }

  .internal-links-tags li a:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-on-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 992px) {
    .internal-links-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .faq-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--sp-xl); }
    .faq-header { position: static; }
    .faq-title { max-width: none; }
    .faq-band { padding: var(--sp-4xl) var(--sp-md); }
    .seo-section { padding: var(--sp-3xl) var(--sp-md); }
    .internal-links-section { padding: var(--sp-3xl) var(--sp-md); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .faq-band { padding: var(--sp-3xl) var(--sp-sm); }
    .seo-section { padding: var(--sp-2xl) var(--sp-sm); }
    .internal-links-section { padding: var(--sp-2xl) var(--sp-sm); }
    details.faq-item summary {
      padding: var(--sp-md) var(--sp-xs);
      font-size: 14px;
      min-height: 44px;
    }
    details.faq-item .faq-body p {
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 22px;
    }
    .internal-link-card { padding: var(--sp-md); }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const items = document.querySelectorAll('details.faq-item');

  items.forEach((detail) => {
    const summary = detail.querySelector('summary');
    const body = detail.querySelector('.faq-body') as HTMLElement | null;

    if (!summary || !body) return;

    summary.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const isOpen = detail.hasAttribute('open');

      if (!isOpen) {
        detail.setAttribute('open', '');
        const h = body.scrollHeight;
        body.style.height = '0px';
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
          body.style.height = h + 'px';
          body.addEventListener('transitionend', () => {
            body.style.height = 'auto';
          }, { once: true });
        });
      } else {
        body.style.height = body.scrollHeight + 'px';
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
          body.style.height = '0px';
          body.addEventListener('transitionend', () => {
            detail.removeAttribute('open');
          }, { once: true });
        });
      }
    });
  });
</script>
